To make life a little easier, the navbars and content pages are generated by Jekyll. Styles and templates are from Bootstrap.

Use HTML to add content to this page. --> it's named 'index.html' in the repo.

Use markdown to add content to the other pages. --> they're named 'some-name.md' in the repo. when the site is served, they'll be rendered as somename/index.html.

And don't forget to replace this landing page content with real information! This is just placeholder stuff.
